chennai (formerly madras) — main port in southern india, cradle of carnatic music and bharatanatyam, home of the famous marina beach, automobile capital of india and a fast emerging it hub. jaipur — the pink city is a major exhibit of the hindu rajput culture of medieval northern india. kochi (formerly cochin) — the queen of arabian sea, historically, a centre of international trade, now the gateway to the sandy beaches and backwaters. kolkata (formerly calcutta) — the cultural capital of india, kolkata is home to numerous colonial buildings. it is known as the city of joy. mumbai (formerly 'bombay) 